\begin_layout Itemize
Alm, McClelland & Schulze calibrate A-S to the US data.
 With coeff of RRA 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma=3$
\end_inset

, they get 13% compliance (waaaaaay off)
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Slemrod (2007) estimates 43% compliance for self-reported income in the
 US
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Calibrations require 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma=5$
\end_inset

 to get 44% compliance, 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma=10$
\end_inset

 to get 71% compliance
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Suggests the theory is incomplete.
\end_layout

