Tax Evasion at the Top of the Income Distribution: Theory and Evidence
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Guyton 
\emph on
et al.

\emph default
 (2021): Motivation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
How much (personal income) tax evasion is there in the US?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
How is it distributed? Do the rich evade more or less than lower-income
 households?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
This paper: 
\series default
Combine multiple data sources to estimate the extent of evasion through
 the income distribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Find that audits do not detect all evasion, especially at the very top.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
At the very top, evasion through pass-through businesses and offshore sheltering
 more common
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Theory to explain this; methodology to measure tax gap correctly.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Guytan 
\emph on
et al.

\emph default
 (2021): Noncompliance in Random Audits
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
IRS runs the 
\emph on
National Research Program 
\emph default
(NRP) that conducts 
\emph on
random
\emph default
 audits of individual tax returns (form 1040).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
NRP does stratified random sampling, oversampling top earners.
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Auditors go through the 1040 using its schedules, 3rd-party reports, taxpayer's
 own records, risk measures comparing the return to other filers.
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Audits known not to be able to detect all evasion.
 IRS has a methodology, 
\emph on
detection-controlled estimation
\emph default
 (DCE), to estimate 
\emph on
undetected
\emph default
 evasion.
 used to estimate aggregate tax gap.
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Pool data from NRP audits 2006–2013: 105,167 audited taxpayers; of whom
 12,003 are in top 1%
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On aggregate, NRP finds 4.0% of true income is under-reported; 7.7% of taxes
 owed are not paid (before DCE correction)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout PlainFrame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename ../../../../Dropbox/Teaching/Princeton PhD Public/Slides/3-TaxCompliance/GuytonEtAl_01.png
	lyxscale 70
	height 98pheight%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout PlainFrame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename ../../../../Dropbox/Teaching/Princeton PhD Public/Slides/3-TaxCompliance/GuytonEtAl_02.png
	lyxscale 70
	height 98pheight%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Guyton 
\emph on
et al.

\emph default
 (2021):Applying DCE Correction
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Detection-Controlled Estimation 
\emph default
(DCE) correction is used to scale up evasion detected in NRP.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Based on Feinstein (1991) model fraction of evasion detected depending on
 return characteristics (types of income, presence of schedules) and examiner
 (experience, age etc).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
After DCE correction, estimated total evasion is 14.0% of true income is
 under-reported; 20.0% of owed taxes are not paid.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
