Guyton 
\emph on
et al.

\emph default
 (2021): Pass-through Business Income Evasion
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Pass-through businesses (S-corporations & partnerships) don't pay corporate
 income tax, their income flows through to their owners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Business ownership highly concentrated at the top of the income distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Much harder to audit since need to flow up to the underlying businesses'
 returns.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
To estimate impact on distribution of evasion follow 2 steps:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Make an assumption about overall evasion rate.
 Benchmark 20% of pass-through income, 5% of pass-through capital gains,
 3% of pass-through dividends
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Assume undetected income is distributed the same way as reported pass-through
 income.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
