\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Modify the welfare effect of the revenue neutral reform to reflect the fact
 that the tax rate reform applies to the top tax bracket only
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dW=\left(\tau\frac{dz}{d\alpha}-\frac{da}{d\alpha}\right)\frac{1}{1-\frac{\tau}{1-\tau}\rho\varepsilon_{1-\tau}}-\frac{d\gamma}{d\alpha}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Taxable income elasticity implies 
\begin_inset Formula $1/\left(1-\frac{\tau}{1-\tau}\rho\hat{\varepsilon}_{1-\tau}\right)=1.51$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
net revenue effect 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau\frac{dz}{d\alpha}-\frac{da}{d\alpha}$
\end_inset

 is 2 orders of magniture larger than 
\begin_inset Formula $da/d\alpha$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Suggests 
\begin_inset Formula $d\gamma/d\alpha$
\end_inset

 would need to be massive for 
\begin_inset Formula $dW<0$
\end_inset

.
 Surveys suggest 
\begin_inset Formula $d\gamma/d\alpha$
\end_inset

 may well have been negative.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
